OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777428225
OL,3,CMPs vote against investigation into
OL,4,Cwhether Starmer misled parliament
OL,6,FMPs have rejected an investigation
OL,7,Finto whether the prime minister misled
OL,8,Fparliament in his characterisation of
OL,9,FPeter Mandelson's appointment as
OL,10,FWashington Ambassador.
OL,12,FIn a vote on Tuesday afternoon, MPs
OL,13,Fopposed referring the PM to the
OL,14,FCommons Privileges Committee, after
OL,15,FLabour backbenchers came together
OL,16,Funder a party whip to reject it.
OL,18,FThe final numbers stood at 223 to and
OL,19,F335 against referring Starmer to the
OL,20,Fcommittee, a majority of 112.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
