PN,31602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777428225
OL,3,CMPs vote against investigation into
OL,4,Cwhether Starmer misled parliament
OL,6,FFollowing the vote, Conservative
OL,7,FLeader Kemi Badenoch said Labour MPs
OL,8,Fwill "rue the day" they voted against
OL,9,Freferring Sir Keir Starmer to the
OL,10,FPrivileges Committee.
OL,12,FCommons Speaker Sir Lindsay Hoyle said
OL,13,Fsome MPs had complained they were
OL,14,Fheckled with shouts of 'shame' as they
OL,15,Fvoted, and urged those responsible to
OL,16,Fapologise.
OL,26,@pD@FOUpD@RO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
