OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777428225
OL,3,CMPs vote against investigation into
OL,4,Cwhether Starmer misled parliament
OL,6,FKemi Badenoch said it was a "disgrace
OL,7,Fthat 333 Labour MPs chose to be
OL,8,Fcomplicit in that cover up", following
OL,9,Fthe outcome of the vote.
OL,11,F"To save his own skin, Keir Starmer
OL,12,Fthreatened his MPs with the loss of
OL,13,Ftheir jobs unless they helped cover up
OL,14,Fhis misleading statements to
OL,15,FParliament," she said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777428225
OL,3,CMPs vote against investigation into
OL,4,Cwhether Starmer misled parliament
OL,6,F"It is very notable that the Chief
OL,7,FSecretary to the Prime Minister would
OL,8,Fnot repeat his boss's claim that there
OL,9,F'was no pressure whatsoever' from No
OL,10,F10 on the appointment of Peter
OL,11,FMandelson.
OL,13,F"This is a government coming apart at
OL,14,Fthe seams. They are more interested in
OL,15,Ftheir own survival than the cost of
OL,16,Fliving crisis affecting hardworking
OL,17,Ffamilies."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
