OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777428225
OL,3,CMPs vote against investigation into
OL,4,Cwhether Starmer misled parliament
OL,6,FWhen former prime minister Boris
OL,7,FJohnson faced a similar vote on
OL,8,Fmisleading parliament over lockdown
OL,9,Fparties in Downing Street during the
OL,10,FCovid pandemic, anger from his own
OL,11,Fbackbenches led him to waive the vote
OL,12,Fthrough unopposed by his own MPs.
OL,14,FThis investigation would later find he
OL,15,Fhad misled parliament and recommend a
OL,16,Ften-week suspension from the House as
OL,17,Fan MP.
OL,19,FJohnson resigned before a vote could
OL,20,Fbe taken on whether to implement this
OL,21,Fsanction.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
