PN,31610
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777428225
OL,3,CMPs vote against investigation into
OL,4,Cwhether Starmer misled parliament
OL,6,FThe claims Starmer stood accused of
OL,7,Fmisleading MPs over were addressed by
OL,8,Fboth the former permanent under
OL,9,Fsecretary in the Foreign Office, Sir
OL,10,FPhilip Barton, and Starmer's ex-chief
OL,11,Fof staff Morgan McSweeney.
OL,13,FMcSweeney denied he had exerted
OL,14,Fpressure on the Foreign Office to
OL,15,Fapprove Mandelson's security clearance
OL,16,F"at any cost", and Barton's testimony
OL,17,Fsupported this, drawing a distinction
OL,18,Fbetween pressure to complete the
OL,19,Fprocess and pressure to reach a
OL,20,Fcertain decision.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31611
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777428225
OL,3,CMPs vote against investigation into
OL,4,Cwhether Starmer misled parliament
OL,6,FOn the latter, Barton denied that had
OL,7,Fbeen the case.
OL,9,FOn the issue of whether "due process"
OL,10,Fhad been followed, Barton did,
OL,11,Fhowever, say it was not normal for the
OL,12,Fappointment to be announced before
OL,13,Fcompleting security vetting, as had
OL,14,Fbeen advised by the then cabinet
OL,15,Fsecretary Simon Case.
OL,17,FParliament will break later this week
OL,18,Fahead of May's local elections.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
